# =============================================================================
# ladder — "Every Wall needs a Ladder".  Self-hosted alternative to 12ft.io
#          and 1ft.io: an HTTP proxy that strips paywalls, removes CORS
#          headers, and bypasses Cloudflare/Akamai/Sucuri WAFs for any
#          website by impersonating Googlebot's user-agent and request
#          headers.  Drop the URL into ladder's web UI or proxy it via
#          /raw/<url> and read articles you'd otherwise hit a wall on.
#          Ships as a single Go binary with rulesets defined in YAML —
#          per-domain overrides for which scripts to block, which CSS
#          to strip, which DOM elements to remove.  Runs in Docker, on
#          systemd, on bare metal, or as a Fly.io / Railway / Render
#          tenant; the canonical self-hosted paywall-bypass appliance.
#
# Author:  Everywall (everywall organization on GitHub).  Project started
#          as a community response to 12ft.io and 1ft.io getting taken
#          down by news-organization legal pressure — ladder revives the
#          functionality as a SELF-HOSTABLE service that no third party
#          can shut down.
# Source:  https://github.com/everywall/ladder
# CLI:     cmd/main.go (uses akamensky/argparse)
# Library: akamensky/argparse
#          ("Argparse for golang. Just because `flag` sucks" —
#           Andrii Kamenskyi's faithful Python argparse port for Go)
